The paper deals with a statistical estimation problem related to learning, specifically in the context of Expectation Maximization (EMX) and Boolean functions. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses combinatorial structures and sample compression schemes, which are relevant to discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS, cs.CC). Finally, the paper explores the existence of a VC-dimension-like parameter, which is a common concept in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
